    "There are four techniques to effectively implement MI [55]:( (4) Summaries: Use summaries not only to encapsulate discussions but also to highlight progress.MI is an evidence-based practice for substance use disorders and other addiction issues [6,12].",
    "It is also found to be effective in helping people adapt to various situations, such as managing diabetes [23,25,44].",
    "Growing research has shown that the combination of CBT and MI shows effectiveness in a variety of populations and for mental health adjustments [14,44,51,53].",
    "Mental Wellness Self-Screening and Self-CareThere are various methods for mental health self-screening [18,47].",
    "While online help-seeking is preferred by many individuals [38], these tools provide a limited assessment based on closed-ended questions, potentially leading to omitting important details typically obtained from open-ended questions or in-person interactions [1,78]."
